# Clean Code Rules

General:
- Prefer simple, explicit and maintainable code.
- Do not over-engineer the MVP.
- Avoid large files.
- Avoid deeply nested conditionals.
- Extract business rules into services/use cases.
- Use descriptive names.
- Do not use magic numbers without constants.
- Prefer early returns.
- Do not duplicate business logic across layers.

Backend:
- Use TypeScript types intentionally.
- Avoid `any` unless there is no practical alternative.
- Keep controllers thin.
- Keep use cases explicit.
- Keep Prisma in infrastructure.
- Keep OpenAI in infrastructure.
- Do not leak Prisma implementation details into controllers.

Comments:
- Comment why, not what.
- Document non-obvious betting, AI and risk rules.

Refactoring:
- Before adding code, inspect existing patterns.
- Prefer extending current conventions over replacing architecture.
